# Testing rules

Framework: Vitest. Full policy in `ENGINEERING.md` D3.

- Every exported function: at least one happy-path and one failure-path test.
- **Never** weaken, skip (`.skip`, `.todo` on existing tests), or delete a test to make a change pass. A failing test means your change is wrong, or you flag the task in `DEVIATIONS.md`.
- LLM-dependent code tests use `FakeBrain` (scripted, deterministic). Real-model tests only under `test/live/` guarded by `LIVE_TESTS=1`, never in CI.
- Golden files (`runtime/test/golden/`) change only with explicit justification in the PR description — byte-identical self-composition is a spec property, not an implementation detail.
- Conformance vectors (`spec/*/vectors/`) are shared law; extending them is encouraged, editing existing vectors requires a spec change in the same PR.
- No mocked crypto. No network in tests. No time/randomness flakiness — inject clocks and seeds.
- Door adapters need the scripted end-to-end residency integration test (arrive → messages → distill → cosign → depart → chain verifies).
